[% META
        title = "Template Documentation"
   description = "Documentation for system templates"
   roles = "admin,developer"
   TemplateType = "Documentation"
   category = "templates"
   page_version = "0.07"
   last_updated = "Tue Apr 22 2026"
   site_specific = "false"
%]
# all links must be Documentation/DocumentationTemplate format
[% PageVersion = 'Documentation/documentation_tt_template.tt,v 0.05 2025/12/18 shanta Exp shanta - Added comprehensive TOC navigation system with section anchors' %]
[% IF c.session.debug_mode == 1 %]
    [% PageVersion %]
[% END %]

<div class="container">
    <h1 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">Documentation Page Title</h1>
    
    <div class="last-updated" style="color: var(--text-muted-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
        Last Updated: 2025-10-15 | 
        Version: 0.02 |
        Author: [Author Name] | 
        Status: [Status]
    </div>

    <!-- TABLE OF CONTENTS SECTION -->
    <div id="toc" class="row" style="margin: var(--spacing-large) 0; background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-left: 4px solid var(--primary-color); border-radius: 4px;">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 0;">Quick Navigation</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-muted-color); font-family: var(--body-font); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">Jump to section:</p>
            <div style="display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: var(--spacing-small);">
                <a href="#overview" style="color: var(--nav-text); text-decoration: none; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 3px; background-color: var(--nav-bg); display: inline-block;">Overview</a>
                <a href="#prerequisites" style="color: var(--nav-text); text-decoration: none; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 3px; background-color: var(--nav-bg); display: inline-block;">Prerequisites</a>
                <a href="#features" style="color: var(--nav-text); text-decoration: none; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 3px; background-color: var(--nav-bg); display: inline-block;">Key Features</a>
                <a href="#getting-started" style="color: var(--nav-text); text-decoration: none; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 3px; background-color: var(--nav-bg); display: inline-block;">Getting Started</a>
                <a href="#advanced" style="color: var(--nav-text); text-decoration: none; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 3px; background-color: var(--nav-bg); display: inline-block;">Advanced Usage</a>
                <a href="#troubleshooting" style="color: var(--nav-text); text-decoration: none; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 3px; background-color: var(--nav-bg); display: inline-block;">Troubleshooting</a>
                <a href="#config-ref" style="color: var(--nav-text); text-decoration: none; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 3px; background-color: var(--nav-bg); display: inline-block;">Configuration</a>
                <a href="#see-also" style="color: var(--nav-text); text-decoration: none; padding: 4px 8px; border-radius: 3px; background-color: var(--nav-bg); display: inline-block;">See Also</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- OVERVIEW SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="overview" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">1. Overview</h2>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Brief overview of what this documentation covers. This should be 1-2 sentences explaining the purpose and scope.</p>
            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- PREREQUISITES & KEY FEATURES SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-50">
            <h2 id="prerequisites" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">2. Prerequisites</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Requirement 1</li>
                <li>Requirement 2</li>
                <li>System access level needed</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="col-50">
            <h2 id="features" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">3. Key Features</h2>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li><strong>Feature 1</strong>: Description of feature</li>
                <li><strong>Feature 2</strong>: Description of feature</li>
                <li><strong>Feature 3</strong>: Description of feature</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- GETTING STARTED SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="getting-started" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">4. Getting Started</h2>
            
            <h3 id="gs-step1" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">4.1 Step 1: Initial Setup</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Detailed instructions for the first step.</p>
            
            <div style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 4px; margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; margin: 0;"><code>
# Example code or command
example_command --parameter value
                </code></pre>
            </div>

            <h3 id="gs-step2" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">4.2 Step 2: Configuration</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Instructions for configuration step.</p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Configure option A</li>
                <li>Set parameter B</li>
                <li>Verify setting C</li>
            </ul>

            <h3 id="gs-step3" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">4.3 Step 3: Verification</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">How to verify everything is working correctly.</p>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ADVANCED USAGE SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="advanced" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">5. Advanced Usage</h2>
            
            <h3 id="adv-feature1" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">5.1 Advanced Feature 1</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">Description and usage instructions for advanced features.</p>

            <h3 id="adv-integration" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large);">5.2 Integration with Other Systems</h3>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">How this feature integrates with other parts of the application.</p>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TROUBLESHOOTING SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="troubleshooting" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">6. Troubleshooting</h2>
            
            <div class="warning" style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border-left: 4px solid var(--warning-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 4px; margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 id="ts-issue1" style="color: var(--warning-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: 0;">Problem: Common Issue 1</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Description of symptoms</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong> Step by step solution</p>
            </div>

            <div style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border-left: 4px solid var(--info-color, #17a2b8); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 4px; margin: var(--spacing-small) 0;">
                <h3 id="ts-issue2" style="color: var(--info-color, #17a2b8); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: 0;">Problem: Common Issue 2</h3>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms:</strong> Description of symptoms</p>
                <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution:</strong> Step by step solution</p>
            </div>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- CONFIGURATION REFERENCE SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <h2 id="config-ref" style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font);">7. Configuration Reference</h2>
            
            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <tr>
                    <th style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Parameter</th>
                    <th style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Type</th>
                    <th style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Default</th>
                    <th style="background-color: var(--table-header-bg); color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Description</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">parameter_1</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">string</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">"default_value"</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Description of parameter</td>
                </tr>
                <tr style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.12);">
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">parameter_2</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">boolean</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">true</td>
                    <td style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font); padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color);">Description of parameter</td>
                </tr>
            </table>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- SEE ALSO SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <div id="see-also" class="success" style="background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); border-left: 4px solid var(--success-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border-radius: 4px; margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
                <h2 style="color: var(--success-color); font-family: var(--header-font); margin-top: 0;">8. See Also</h2>
                <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                    <li><a href="/Documentation/related_doc_1" style="color: var(--link-color);">Related Documentation 1</a></li>
                    <li><a href="/Documentation/related_doc_2" style="color: var(--link-color);">Related Documentation 2</a></li>
                    <li><a href="/admin" style="color: var(--link-color);">Administrative Interface</a></li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <p style="text-align: right; margin-top: var(--spacing-small);"><a href="#toc" style="color: var(--link-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">↑ Back to Top</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FOOTER SECTION -->
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-100">
            <div style="margin-top: var(--spacing-large); padding-top: var(--spacing-medium); border-top: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-muted-color); font-size: var(--font-size-small);">
                <p>For technical support or questions about this documentation, contact the system administrator.</p>
                <p><em>This documentation is part of the Comserv system.</em></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<!-- 
THEME COMPLIANCE NOTES FOR DEVELOPERS:

This template is fully theme-compliant using the actual Comserv theme system:

1. **Canonical CSS Variables** (defined in static/css/base.css — use ONLY these names):

   COLOURS:
   --primary-color        Brand primary; nav bars, headings           default: #ccffff
   --secondary-color      Muted secondary surfaces                    default: #f9f9f9
   --accent-color         Highlight / call-to-action                  default: #FF9900
   --text-color           Body text and headings                      default: #000000
   --background-color     Page background solid colour                default: #ffffff
   --link-color           Hyperlink colour                            default: #0000FF
   --link-hover-color     Hyperlink hover colour                      default: #000099
   --border-color         Borders and dividers                        default: #cccccc
   --table-header-bg      Table <th> and card header background       default: #f2f2f2
   --success-color        Success / positive state                    default: #009900
   --warning-color        Warning / danger / error state              default: #ff0000
   --info-color           Informational highlights                    default: #17a2b8
   --caution-color        Caution / staging-environment (amber)       default: #ffc107
   --light-color          Very light neutral surface                  default: #f8f9fa
   --text-muted-color     De-emphasised / secondary text (canonical)  default: #6c757d
   --text-muted           Alias → --text-muted-color (compat only)

   BACKGROUND / ALIASES:
   --background-image     Optional background-image URL               default: none
   --bg-color             Alias → --background-color
   --bg-secondary         Alias → --secondary-color
   --card-bg              Alias → --table-header-bg

   NAVIGATION:
   --nav-bg               Nav bar background   → --primary-color
   --nav-text             Nav bar text colour  → --text-color
   --nav-hover-bg         Nav item hover bg    default: rgba(0,0,0,0.1)

   TYPOGRAPHY:
   --header-font          Heading font stack   default: Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif
   --body-font            Body font stack      default: Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif
   --font-size-base       Base font size       default: 16px
   --font-size-small      Small text           default: 14px
   --font-size-large      Large sub-heading    default: 20px
   --font-size-xlarge     Extra-large / hero   default: 24px

   SPACING & LAYOUT:
   --spacing-small        Compact pad/gap      default: 0.5rem
   --spacing-medium       Standard pad/gap     default: 1rem
   --spacing-large        Section pad/gap      default: 2rem
   --container-width      Max page width       default: 1200px

   BUTTONS:
   --button-bg            Button background    default: #f2f2f2
   --button-text          Button text colour   default: #000000
   --button-border        Button border        default: #cccccc
   --button-hover-bg      Button hover bg      default: #e0e0e0

   NAMING RULES:
   - Use canonical names in all new CSS. --text-muted alias is backward-compat only.
   - Never hardcode colours in .tt inline styles; always use var(--name, fallback).
   - Site-specific vars (--bee-yellow etc.) belong in the site's theme file only.
   - Admin-component vars belong in admin.css, delegating to canonical vars.

   CSS Variables Used in this template:
   - --text-color, --background-color, --primary-color, --secondary-color
   - --header-font, --body-font, --font-size-* variables
   - --spacing-small, --spacing-medium, --spacing-large for consistent spacing
   - --border-color, --table-header-bg, --warning-color, --success-color, --info-color

2. **Layout System**: Uses the responsive grid system from layout.css:
   - .container for main content wrapper
   - .row for horizontal groupings
   - .col-100, .col-50 for responsive column layouts

3. **Color-Coded Content Blocks**: 
   - Warning blocks use --warning-color with left border accent
   - Info blocks use --info-color with left border accent  
   - Success blocks use --success-color with left border accent

4. **Responsive Design**: Layout automatically adapts on mobile using layout.css media queries

5. **Theme Variables Available**:
   From theme_definitions.json, any site can override:
   - Colors: primary-color, secondary-color, accent-color, text-color, etc.
   - Typography: header-font, body-font, font-size-base, font-size-large, etc.
   - UI Elements: button-bg, nav-bg, table-header-bg, border-color, etc.

6. **Cross-Theme Compatibility**: Works correctly with:
   - Default theme (standard blue/white)
   - CSC theme (cyan backgrounds)  
   - USBM theme (green accent colors)
   - APIS theme (yellow/orange beekeeping theme)
   - Any future themes added to theme_definitions.json

7. **Navigation Features** (NEW in v0.05):
   - Table of Contents (id="toc") with quick-jump navigation buttons
   - Anchor links (id attributes) on all major sections (1-8)
   - Subsection anchors for Getting Started (4.1-4.3), Advanced Usage (5.1-5.2), Troubleshooting (6.1-6.2)
   - "Back to Top" links after each major section for easy navigation
   - All navigation uses CSS variables for theme consistency
   - Self-contained: Works standalone or via template inclusion directive (no relative paths)

8. **DOCUMENTATION LINK FORMAT** (CRITICAL - See .zencoder/rules/DOCUMENTATION_LINK_STANDARDS.md):
   - CORRECT: <a href="/Documentation/FILENAME">Link Text</a>
   - WRONG: <a href="/Documentation/system/FILENAME.tt">...</a> (DO NOT include subdirectory or .tt extension)
   - Documentation system uses flat namespace: strip .tt extension, ignore subdirectories
   - Example: /Documentation/system/DOCKER_KUBERNETES_MIGRATION_STRATEGY.tt → /Documentation/DOCKER_KUBERNETES_MIGRATION_STRATEGY
   - For non-documentation links (admin, todo, etc.) use full path as-is: <a href="/admin">Admin</a>
   - See .zencoder/rules/DOCUMENTATION_LINK_STANDARDS.md for authoritative reference and routing details

Usage: Replace placeholder content but maintain the CSS variable usage patterns and section anchors. When adding links to other documentation, use /Documentation/FILENAME format (no subdirectories, no .tt extension).
-->